description: Common on sandspit at forested dune edge and open backdunes. In the beach photo, Avenella is the coppery, wispy grass with thread-like leaves.

The bronze-colored, wispy grass in the photo. Thin, thread-like, dark green basal leaves. Relatively common along new boardwalk and in older dune areas on the west end of Long Island, but less common here than on many other sandscapes. It becomes out-competed quickly by common juniper or the habitat is better in the foredunes for Ammophila breviligulata or wetland swale vegetation.
